<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ880718-0106 </DOCNO><HL> Cyprus Minerals Co. Plans Issue </HL><SO> </SO><CO> CYPM </CO><IN> STK </IN><DATELINE> DENVER  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Cyprus Minerals Co. said it registered with the Securities and Exchange Commission to offer three million shares of convertible exchangeable preferred stock, Series B at $50 a share.    The rate of conversion will be determined at the time of the final pricing.    The mining company, which has about 26 million common shares outstanding, said proceeds will be used to pay bank debt and for general corporate purposes.    First Boston Corp. is the underwriter. </TEXT></DOC>